  that minimizes this expectation value, thereby preparing a quantum state ‚à£œà( 
Œ∏

 )‚ü© that is the best possible approximation of the true ground state, given the constraints of the trial wavefunction's structure. This structure is defined by a parameterized quantum circuit, often called an ansatz.

This principle is operationalized through a hybrid quantum-classical feedback loop, which forms the backbone of algorithms like QAOA and the Variational Quantum Eigensolver (VQE):

Classical Initialization: A classical computer chooses an initial set of parameters,  
