Lists).309.2 Electrical and Logic Schematics (IEEE 315 & 991 Compliant): A complete set of schematic and logic diagrams will define the electrical and avionics systems. These will be prepared in accordance with IEEE Std 315 (Graphic Symbols for Electrical and Electronics Diagrams) and IEEE Std 991 (Logic Circuit Diagrams) to ensure clarity and standardization.339.3 Configuration Management Plan (per MIL-HDBK-61A): To ensure the integrity and control of the design baseline, a formal Configuration Management (CM) Plan will be executed, guided by the principles of MIL-HDBK-61A, Configuration Management Guidance.37 This plan will establish procedures for configuration identification, control, status accounting, and audits (FCA/PCA).28By defining the structure and governing standards of the TDP from the outset, this program is oriented not just toward a successful scientific demonstration, but toward delivering a mature, well-documented, and transition-ready product to the Department of DefenseDOCUMENT ID: KSS-DOD-USF-AETHELRED-MASTER-2025-Rev.A CLASSIFICATION: FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY (FOUO) SUBJECT: The complete technical framework for the Project Sovereign Aethelred platform, a 6th-generation multi-domain asset integrating the Unified Sovereignty Framework (USF) architecture. This document provides the definitive, non-fictional blueprint for a warfighter engineered for post-quantum strategic dominance, with all subsystems defined by current scientific principles and mathematical models.

Abstract
This document presents the technical architecture for the Sovereign Aethelred platform, a revolutionary system designed to solve the foundational crises of modern warfare: cognitive overload, network fragility, and the existential threat of quantum computing. This is not an incremental upgrade to legacy systems but a paradigm shift, integrating a suite of interlocking technologies into a single, cohesive, and operational warfighting ecosystem. By fusing a Gen-5 eidomorphic command interface with a post-quantum computational core and a multi-layered sovereign communications network, the Sovereign Aethelred platform ensures that the operator can perceive, decide, and act with unprecedented speed and clarity. The entire system is built upon a formally verified assurance framework to guarantee mathematical security and is designed to serve as the central, crewed node in a distributed, human-machine combat team. This dossier details the five core layers of the platform: the Human Interface, the Communications Layer, the Security & Computation Layer, the Physical Airframe, and the Integrated Armament Suite.

Layer 1: The Human Interface ‚Äî The Cognitive Cockpit
The primary design principle is the mitigation of operator cognitive load by transforming the human-computer interface from a data-reporting tool into a cognitive partner. This is achieved through a multi-modal interface that leverages established principles of human perception and neurophysiology.   

1.1 Gen-5 Strategic Command System (Eido-morphic Overlay): The traditional instrument panel is eliminated in favor of a full-color, wide field-of-view Augmented Reality Helmet-Mounted Display (AR-HMD). This system provides a 360-degree "see-through-the-plane" view by fusing data from a distributed aperture system, similar to the F-35 Gen III HMDS. The interface design is governed by Gestalt psychology to reduce extraneous cognitive load.

Mathematical & Scientific Basis: The goal is to minimize the mental effort required to process information. The layout uses principles like Proximity (grouping related data), Similarity (using common colors/shapes for elements with similar functions), and Common Region (using enclosures like cards to unify disparate data points into a single perceived group) to create an intuitive visual hierarchy. This allows the operator's brain to process information as holistic patterns rather than discrete data points, facilitating faster comprehension. The randomness and complexity of the operator's visual scan pattern can be quantified by its entropy, calculated as:   

