Section 2.0: Propulsion Architecture and Performance Envelope

2.1 The Adaptive Engine Core: Next Generation Adaptive Propulsion (NGAP)

The heart of the F-47 platform is a propulsion system derived from the U.S. Air Force's Next Generation Adaptive Propulsion (NGAP) program, for which General Electric is developing the XA102 and Pratt & Whitney is developing the XA103. This program is the technological successor to the highly successful Adaptive Engine Transition Program (AETP), which validated the core technologies in the XA100 and XA101 demonstrators. The NGAP engine represents a paradigm shift through its variable cycle, three-stream architecture.

