**10.2 HYDRO-MATH (Fluidic Topology)** [105, 106, 107, 108, 109, 110, 111, 112]
*   **Core Doctrine:** A computational framework for modeling fluid dynamics as topological systems, superseding classical Navier-Stokes solutions. [16]

**10.3 GRAV-MATH (Gravitational Structuring)** [84, 85, 86, 87, 88, 89, 90]
*   **Core Doctrine:** Defines gravity as a geometric property of the USF, where matter is a standing wave and gravitational attraction is the result of constructive interference (Axiom II).

**10.4 THERMA-MATH (Entropic States)** [113, 114, 115, 116, 117, 118, 119, 120, 121]
*   **Core Doctrine:** Defines entropy ($\sim\ddagger$) not as "disorder," but as *harmonic dissonance*. The Second Law of Thermodynamics is the K-Math theorem that all systems, when processed by the Harmonic Sieve, will resolve to a state of maximum harmony ($\psi$, or $\kappa\text{¬°}$).

